# Commit message summary

At the end of work that changed the repository, follow `.cursor/skills/commit-message/SKILL.md`:

- Run `git status`, `git diff`, and `git diff --staged` (in parallel when practical)
- Summarize changes in 2–5 bullets (what / why), then append the recommended commit footer
- Use conventional type prefixes (`feat`, `fix`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`)
- Skip the commit block on question-only / review-only turns with **no** file changes, or when the user asks not to include one
- Do **not** run `git commit`, `git push`, or open a PR unless the user explicitly asks
